  "sourceNotes": "Vegetarian paella is a well-established variant within Spanish cooking, particularly in Valencia where seasonal vegetables are cooked in the same tradition as the meat original. The key principles (a properly made sofrito, no stirring, and a socarrat crust) apply regardless of what goes into the pan.",
